FBIS4-53506 "dreas098_b_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-098 Daily Report 17 May 1994 Mongolia Foreign Ministry Protests Mistreatment of Diplomat Foreign Ministry Protests Mistreatment of Diplomat LD1705083294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0811 GMT 17 May 94 LD1705083294 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Ulaanbaatar May 17 ITAR-TASS -- The Mongolian Foreign Ministry has delivered a note of protest to the Russian envoy to Mongolia in connection with the assault on, and robbery of Mongolian Vice-Consul in Buriatiya Batsuur and several persons who accompanied him near the Ubienny mountain pass near the town of Gusinoozersk on May 11. According to the note, the Mongols were robbed of cash, valuables and official documents. Batsuur suffered serious injuries, despite the fact that he had identified himself as a consular employee. The Mongolian Foreign Ministry expressed the hope that the criminals who violated the Mongolian consular employee's diplomatic immunity will be identified and brought to account, the press-service of the Mongolian Foreign Ministry said.
